  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA29-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu makaṭ pōkkiya tāy colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what is said by the mother who had let [her] daughter go.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA29">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            niṉṟa vēṉi lulanta kānta </l>
<l>            ḷaḻalavir nīḷiṭai niḻaliṭam peṟāa</l>
<l>            tīṉṟukāṉ maṭinta piṇavuppaci kūrnteṉa</l>
<l>            māṉṟa mālai vaḻaṅkunarc cekīiya</l>
<l>            pulipārt tuṟaiyum pullatarc ciṟuneṟi </l>
<l>            yāṅkuval lunaḷko ṟāṉē yāṉṟaṉ</l>
<l>            vaṉaintēn tiḷamulai nōva kolleṉa </l>
<l>            niṉaintukain nekiḻnta vaṉaittaṟkut tāṉṟaṉ</l>
<l>            pēramar maḻaikka ṇīriya kaluḻa</l>
<l>            veyya vuyirkkuñ cāyaṉ </l>
<l>            maiyī rōtip perumaṭat takaiyē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>How is she able [to go], she,</l>
<l rend="indent">on the little grassy [and] sandy path</l>
<l rend="indent2">where the doe, having [just] given birth, feet drooping, stays,</l>
<l rend="indent3">after seeing the tiger, that has destroyed wanderers</l>
<l rend="indent3">in gloomy evening because [its] hunger is waxing,</l>
<l rend="indent2">without obtaining a shady place on the long way of shining fire,</l>
<l rend="indent2">with Malabar lilies dead from permanent summer?</l>
<l>– [she who] is prone to great folly,</l>
<l>of kajal[-coloured] moist hair,</l>
<l>the graceful [one](?)<note place="foot">How to include <term xml:lang="ta">cāyal</term> into this construction?</note>, who breathes hot [sighs]</l>
<l rend="indent">while her large, beautiful rain eyes dim so as to become wet</l>
<l rend="indent">about the embrace of [my] hand becoming loose in the thought</l>
<l rend="indent2">“do [her] eminent young breasts ache, as I embrace them?”</l>
        
       </lg>
         </div>
